  "text": "Computing the residual correlations of non-stationary signals has been previously studied in various domains [CITATION_1] . Commonly, the trend is modelled in a parametric or non-parametric way, which allows subtracting the underlying population trend. Often, trends are assumed to be linear, and the method of partial correlations is used to compute the trend-corrected fluctuations (see Methods for details). The expression trends in our data are far from linear, and we therefore take a non-linear detrending approach.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "16676760"
